-- Lonmin Worker Goes Missing at South Africa's Marikana, Labor Union Says
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2010-11-17T09:55:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-17/lonmin-worker-goes-missing-at-south-africa-s-marikana-labor-union-says.html
A miner went missing at Lonmin Plc’s
Karee mine in South Africa yesterday, the National Union of
Mineworkers said.  A rescue team is searching for the worker, who went missing
at the Rustenburg-based mine’s Marikana K3 shaft, the labor
union said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  